cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper deals with optimization techniques for machine learning, specifically gradient descent and coordinate descent. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the boundedness of correlations between eigenfeatures and the response variable, which suggests a possible connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions heuristics for non-convex optimization, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions deep learning, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
